Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 350 degrees. Wash and dry produce (be sure to dry the @kale{4%ounce} thoroughly so it crisps up in the oven!).

Remove and discard any large stems from kale. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ¼-inch-thick pieces. Quarter @lemon{1}.

Toss kale on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{}, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. 

> TIP: For easy cleanup, line baking sheet with aluminum foil first.

Roast on top rack until browned and crisp, ~{13-15%minutes}. (For 4 servings, divide kale between 2 #baking sheets{}. Roast on top and middle racks, switching rack positions halfway through.)

While kale roasts, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

== Turmeric-Toasted Couscous ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @Israeli couscous{5%ounce} and @turmeric{1%tsp}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant and toasted, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add @veggie stock concentrate{1}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a big pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until liquid has absorbed and couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}. Keep covered until ready to serve.

== Maple Carrots ==

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add carrots, @harissa powder{1%tbsp}, salt, and pepper.

> TIP: If you prefer a milder flavor, use less harissa powder.

Cook, stirring occasionally, until just softened, ~{5-8%minutes}. Add @maple syrup{2%tbsp} and @water{2%tbsp}; cook, stirring occasionally, until carrots are lightly browned and tender, ~{3-5%minutes}. Remove pan from heat.

> Use pan used for chicken here.

== Lemony Hummus ==

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @hummus{1/2%cup}, @tahini{1%tbsp}, juice from one lemon wedge, @olive oil{1%tbsp}, and @water{1%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper.

== Assembly ==

Fluff couscous with a #fork{}; stir in a drizzle of @olive oil{}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide couscous between #bowls{}. Top with kale, carrots, hummus, @dried cranberries{1%ounce}, and @walnuts{1/2%ounce}. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

Slice chicken crosswise; serve atop bowls.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.